cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CC 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques to identify principled recurring arguments for competitive debaters. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves the use of AI and machine learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves classification and identification of relevant arguments, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to identify relevant arguments, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves the use of computational techniques to facilitate automatic argument invention, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
